<HEADLINE>
<P>
BEN HILL GRIFFIN; FLORIDA CITRUS BARON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Florida citrus baron Ben Hill Griffin, 79, listed in Forbes magazine as one of 
the 400 richest Americans. In October, Forbes put him 261st on the list of 
wealthy Americans and said he was worth $390 million. 
</P>
<P>
Griffin, a member of the Florida Legislature for 12 years, started his citrus 
empire in 1933, when his father gave him 10 acres of groves as a wedding 
present. His company, Ben Hill Griffin Inc., owned more than 10,000 acres of 
citrus groves and 85,000 acres of ranch and timberland in central Florida. The 
Griffin family sold its packinghouses and a huge juice processing plant to 
Procter &amp; Gamble Co. in 1981, which introduced its juice under the Citrus 
Hill brand name. On Thursday in Avon Park, Fla. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Obituary 
</P>
</TYPE>
