<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PLATING COMPANY FIRE CAUSES $50,000 DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire at a Burbank plating company caused $50,000 damage Sunday, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Four fire companies responded to the 9:26 a.m. blaze at A-H Plating in the 1800 
block of Victory Place, said Jean Osmond, a dispatcher for the Burbank Fire 
Department. It was contained within 20 minutes, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
