<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOMELESS IN SANTA MONICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
She talks of meals distributed to the homeless. I would like to tell about my 
meal in an emergency ward recently at Los Angeles County Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
It was symbolic, for I had no money or insurance to pay the bills. I was 
accepted for surgery and in line with other casualties of living. 
</P>
<P>
This is the precious processing of poor patients by dedicated professionals, 
using their skills to stitch and mend our broken bodies. Nurses would brighten 
up blank stares, then take on a surge of questions that the doctor would 
scratch his head over. So much activity! Computers say input, output and 
processed patient; but my God, so many hundreds of people moving to enrich 
life. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN WARREN 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
