<TEXT>
<P>
Greg LeMond returned to cycling competition by finishing 16th in the first 
stage of the Paris-Nice race, the opening major race of the cycling season. 
Second-year pro Francis Moreau won over the 4.2-mile course in eastern Paris in 
9 minutes 15.09 seconds. LeMond's time was 9:42.78. 
</P>
