<TEXT>
<P>
East Germans Jacqueline Boerner and Gunda Kleeman won in the 1,500- and 
5,000-meter races in the final day of the Women's World Cup speed skating event 
at Inzell, West Germany. 
</P>
<P>
Boerner dashed home over 1,500 meters in 2 minutes 10.10 seconds. Bonnie Blair 
of Champaign, Ill., was fourth in 2:10.58. 
</P>
<P>
Kleeman proved fastest over the 5,000 meters, finishing in 7 minutes 54.27 
seconds. 
</P>
