<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SAN DIEGO; 
</P>
<P>
70 ARRESTED IN ANTI-GANG ACTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seventy members and associates of three San Diego Crip gangs have been arrested 
in a yearlong undercover investigation aimed at street-level drug dealers, 
authorities said. "Operation Blue Rag," a federally funded operation targeting 
the gang members, swept a number of suspected drug traffickers from 
neighborhoods with notorious reputations as hangouts for crack cocaine dealing 
and other criminal activity, the San Diego County district attorney's office 
said. Eight of the suspects were arrested on federal charges but the majority 
were booked on state charges involving drug sales and possession of drugs and 
weapons. 
</P>
