<P>
WORKER MAY HAVE SWALLOWED PESTICIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A farm worker who died while spraying an almond orchard apparently swallowed 
some of the pesticide parathion, according to the Kern County coroner's office. 
An autopsy on Jose Campos Martinez, 25, revealed he had an "appreciable 
quantity" of the pesticide in his stomach, but not in his vital organs, 
indicating he must have swallowed the poison and not ingested it through his 
skin or nostrils. Campos, who lived in Wasco, fell dead in an orchard near Lost 
Hills on Jan. 20. 
