<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA REGIONAL PREP BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
MATER DEI GETS NORTH HOLLYWOOD; ESTANCIA FACES TULARE WESTERN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM HAMILTON, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Mater Dei High School boys' basketball team, Southern Section 5-A division 
champion, is the second-seeded team in the Southern California Regional 
Division I playoffs and will play host to North Hollywood Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei (30-1) is assured of home games for the opening two games of the 
eight-team tournament. Tuesday's game will be at Ocean View High School or 
Chapman College, Mater Dei Coach Gary McKnight said. The championship game is 
scheduled for 8:30 p.m. Friday at the Los Angeles Sports Arena. Regional games 
will be played Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday in all divisions except Division 
I. 
</P>
<P>
"Whoever wins, it's a tribute to them with three games in five days," McKnight 
said. "There's no time for preparation, you're just going to have to do what 
you do best if you hope to win." 
</P>
<P>
North Hollywood (23-3), which upset Fremont to win the City 3-A championship, 
is led by 6-foot-6 forward Dana Jones, who had 29 points and 29 rebounds 
against Fremont. 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach Poly (26-2) is the top-seeded team in the division and will play 
host to Loyola (23-4) at Long Beach City College. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia (20-9) is the top-seeded team in Division III and plays host to Tulare 
Western in the first round. Servite (17-11) and Corona del Mar (19-10) also 
gained berths in the division. 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar will play at second-seeded San Diego Lincoln (22-8) and Servite 
will play at LeMoore (18-9) at 8 p.m. in the second game of a doubleheader. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach (22-6), runner-up in the Southern Section's 2-A division, will 
play at Coronado (19-8) in Division IV playoffs. Defending state champion Santa 
Clara (24-0) is the top-seeded team in the division. 
</P>
<P>
In Division V, St. Margaret's (21-5) will play El Cajon Christian (16-11) at 
Granite Hills High. El Cajon Christian is the second-seeded team behind Ribet 
Academy. 
</P>
<P>
Each division winner in the regional playoffs will play the division winners of 
the Northern California Regional playoffs for the state championship March 
16-17 at the Oakland Coliseum Arena. 
</P>
</TEXT>
