<P>
WILLIS IS 'TALKING' BIG MONEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bruce Willis makes a better deal than Donald Trump. 
</P>
<P>
Willis put in only three or four days of work in providing the voice for the 
baby in the movie "Look Who's Talking," but it's going to earn him about $10 
million even though he's never seen in the film, according to Premiere 
magazine. 
</P>
<P>
Instead of a flat salary, Willis agreed to take a percentage of the movie's 
gross, and when "Look Who's Talking" became a surprise hit, he reaped a 
windfall that's double what he earned for starring in "Die Hard." Premiere says 
Willis' take exceeds what it cost to make the movie and is more than the 
producers will make. 
